  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims to compare the efÔ¨Åcacy of two surgical techniques in treatment of complex&#xD;
      anal fistulas. The first technique involves rerouting of the fistula tract with placement of&#xD;
      a vessel loop seton around the internal anal sphincter, sparing the external sphincter&#xD;
      whereas the second technique entails ligation of inter-sphincteric fistulous tract (LIFT).&#xD;
      The main objectives of the study are to assess the success rate, time to healing, change in&#xD;
      quality of life, and complications of each procedure including fecal incontinence.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
